    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "How long does the scan take?",
        "answer": "12–20 minutes; add 10 minutes if contrast is used.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Is contrast injection safe?",
        "answer": "Yes. Gadolinium is FDA-approved; tell us if you have kidney issues.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I eat before the MRI?",
        "answer": "Yes, unless contrast is planned—then light fasting for 4 h.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What if I feel claustrophobic?",
        "answer": "Request open-bore 3T or mild sedation; headphones and music help.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "When will I get my report?",
        "answer": "Same day after 2 p.m. for morning scans; next-day for evening slots."
      },
      {
        "question": "What are the next steps after an MRI CV Junction scan?  ",
        "answer": "Once your referring doctor receives the report for your **MRI CV Junction** scan from Cadabams Diagnostics, they will review the findings in combination with your clinical symptoms, medical history, and any other relevant test results. Based on this comprehensive assessment, they will discuss the diagnosis with you and outline potential treatment options if any abnormalities are found. This might involve further specialist consultations (e.g., with a neurologist or neurosurgeon), medication, physical therapy, or, in some cases, surgical intervention.  "
      }
    ],
